Build a container with R and various packages needed for proteomics analysis.
The container is based on the rocker/r-base image.

# 1. Modify the Dockerfile to install the software

* modify the rocker/r-base version to match the version of R that is required.
* modify the Bioconductor version to match the version of R that is required.
* Add any new packages.

# 2. Build the Docker image

```
version=4.5.1
sudo docker build -t r_base:v${version} .

docker start scrnaseq_rstudio
```

# 3. Build the Singularity image

```
version=4.5.1
sudo singularity build r_base_${version}.sif docker-daemon://r_base:v${version}
```
--> rstudio_scRNAseq_4.5.1.sif
